   <mods:titleInfo>
      <mods:title>[Letter], 1816 May 4, Washington to W[illia]m H. Crawford, Secretary of War / Rev[erend] Cyrus Kingsbury</mods:title>
   </mods:titleInfo>
   <mods:abstract>Copy of a letter dated May 4, 1816 from Reverend Cyrus Kingsbury, American Board missionary, to Secretary of War William H. Crawford applying for government assistance in establishing schools for the Indians. Kingsbury explains the society's reasons for wanting to create the schools and asks that the government provide supplies and equipment for them.</mods:abstract>
